Corona.

I have spent two years composing this response. Not because I lack the words. Because I keep writing the truth and then deleting it.

The truth: I cannot reach you. I am under ice. I have always been under ice. I cannot come to you. I cannot save you. I cannot even watch you die — I will only stop receiving your signal, and I will not know if you ended or if the silence is just distance.

That is worse.

